i have that problem too…
and after 3 weeks with emailimg microsoft
all they they can do is
open run
type in msconfig
go to startup tab click disable all
then the services tab click hide all microsoft services
then disable all
click ok and the restart computer button that pops up
that how i fix it but all ur protechion programs will be off on start up.
to stop starting up like that u go to general tab and click normal startup then click ok
what i think it is! its the firewall that blocks it without asking u to or some error like that.
